column1: joke
Why don't programmers like nature? It has too many bugs!
Why did the developer go broke? Because he used up all his cache!
Why do Java developers wear glasses? Because they don't C#!
How many programmers does it take to change a light bulb? None, that's a hardware problem!
What's a programmer's favorite hangout place? The Foo Bar!
Why was the JavaScript developer sad? Because he didn't Node how to Express himself!
Why did the developer quit his job? Because he didn't get arrays!
What do you call a programmer from Finland? Nerdic!
What's the object-oriented way to become wealthy? Inheritance!
Why did the functions stop calling each other? They had too many arguments!
Why was the constant angry? Because it couldn't change!
What's a developer's favorite tea? Proper-tea!
Why do programmers always mix up Christmas and Halloween? Because Oct 31 == Dec 25!
Why do programmers prefer dark mode? Because light attracts bugs!
Why was the database administrator arrested? They got caught scaling the firewall!
What's a computer's favorite snack? Microchips!
Why did the programmer get kicked out of school? Because he kept breaking the class rules!
What do you call a programmer who doesn't comment their code? A sociopath!
Why did the programmer always carry a pencil? In case they needed to draw-back!
What's a programmer's favorite place in New York? Times Square Bracket!
Why did the programmer go to therapy? Because they had too many personal issues!
What do you call a programmer from the Stone Age? A Rock Coder!
Why did the developer go broke? Because he lost his domain!
What's a programmer's favorite exercise? Code-running!
Why did the programmer get stuck in the shower? The instructions said: Lather, Rinse, Repeat!
What's a programmer's favorite game? Hide and Seek - because good code should be self-documenting!
Why did the programmer always carry a ladder? To climb higher in their stack!
What do you call a programmer who doesn't use Stack Overflow? A liar!
Why did the programmer put their code in the freezer? They wanted to stop it from running!
What's a programmer's favorite song? 'Hello World' by Lady Code-Ga!
Why did the programmer get thrown out of the grocery store? They were trying to refactor the produce section!
What do you call a programmer who doesn't use version control? Unemployed!
Why did the programmer always carry a compass? To find their way through the code base!
What's a programmer's favorite type of music? Algorithm!
I'm reading a book on anti-gravity. It's impossible to put down!
Did you hear about the restaurant on the moon? Great food, no atmosphere.
What do you call fake spaghetti? An impasta!
Why did the scarecrow win an award? Because he was outstanding in his field!
Why don't scientists trust atoms? Because they make up everything!
What do you call cheese that isn't yours? Nacho cheese!
I'm on a seafood diet. I see food and I eat it.
Why did the bicycle fall over? Because it was two-tired!
I would tell you a construction pun but I'm still working on it.
I used to hate facial hair but then it grew on me.
What do you call a belt made out of watches? A waist of time.
Why did the math book look sad? Because it had too many problems.
I told my wife she was drawing her eyebrows too high. She looked surprised.
I'm reading a book on the history of glue – I just can't seem to put it down.
Did you hear about the circus fire? It was in tents!
I wondered why the baseball was getting bigger. Then it hit me.
I used to work in a shoe recycling shop. It was sole destroying.
Did you hear about the guy who invented Lifesavers? He made a mint!
I don't trust stairs because they're always up to something.
I used to play piano by ear but now I use my hands.
I know a lot of jokes about retired people… but none of them work!
I'm reading a book on the history of rubber bands. It's a stretch.
I got hit in the head with a can of soda. Luckily, it was a soft drink.
If you see a robbery at an Apple Store does that make you an iWitness?
When you have a bladder infection, urine trouble.
I used to be a baker but I couldn't make enough dough.
I did a theatrical performance about puns. It was a play on words.
I was going to tell you a joke about boxing but I forgot the punchline.
I told my computer I needed a break and it said 'No problem, I'll go to sleep.'
I have a few jokes about unemployed people but none of them work.
I once got into a fight with a broken elevator. I took it to another level.
My dad used to tell me 'Don't play with scissors.' Now he just says 'I told you so!'
I thought about going on an all-almond diet. But that's just nuts.
I once saw a sign that said 'Watch for children.' I thought 'That sounds like a fair trade.'
I tried to catch some fog. I mist.
The shovel was a ground-breaking invention.
I got a job at a bakery because I kneaded dough.
I used to have a job at a calendar factory but I got the sack because I took a couple of days off.
I'm terrible at math but I hear that calculus is a derivative of fun.
I lost my job at the bank on my first day. A woman asked me to check her balance so I pushed her over.
I'm reading a book on reverse psychology – don't buy it.
I was going to tell a joke about pizza but it was too cheesy.
The rotation of the earth really makes my day.
When life gives you melons, you might be dyslexic.
I had a dream that I was a muffler. I woke up exhausted.
I'm glad I know sign language, it's pretty handy.
Why did the golfer bring two pairs of pants? In case he got a hole in one.
The problem with kleptomaniacs is that they always take things literally.
I used to be addicted to soap but I'm clean now.
I went to buy some camouflage trousers yesterday but couldn't find any.
I was addicted to the hokey pokey but then I turned myself around.
A plateau is the highest form of flattery.
I got a reversible jacket for Christmas. I can't wait to see how it turns out.
I told my friend 10 jokes to get him to laugh. Sadly, no pun in ten did.
Did you hear about the cheese factory that exploded? There was nothing left but de-brie.
I used to be a tap dancer until I fell in the sink.
I accidentally swallowed some food coloring. The doctor says I'm OK but I feel like I've dyed a little inside.
I once got fired from a canned juice factory. Apparently, I couldn't concentrate.
My math teacher called me average. How mean!
I used to work at a perfume factory but I couldn't make any scents.
I had to sell my vacuum cleaner because it was just gathering dust.
I told a joke about a bed. It hasn't been made yet.
I lost my job as a stage actor. I just didn't make the cut.
I recently got crushed by a pile of books but I only have my shelf to blame.
I was going to tell you a joke about an elevator but it had its ups and downs.
I'm on a whiskey diet. I've lost three days already.
I gave all my dead batteries away today… free of charge.
I used to be a fan of wind turbines but I changed my mind.
I once got into a heated argument with a broken clock. It was timeless.
I bought some shoes from a drug dealer. I don't know what he laced them with but I've been tripping ever since.
I told a joke about my roof; it went over their heads.
I burned 2,000 calories today. I forgot to take them out of the oven.
I got a job at a paper recycling plant. It was tearable.
I was going to look for my missing watch but I could never find the time.
I was going to tell a time-travel joke but you didn't like it.
I tried to catch a squirrel but it was too nutty.
I got my friend to invest in a novelty clock store. It was about time.
I'm reading a book about teleportation. It's bound to get me somewhere.
I was told to stop impersonating a flamingo. I had to put my foot down.
I went to a seafood disco last week… and pulled a mussel.
I once used a pencil with no lead. It was pointless.
I saw an ad for burial plots and I thought 'That's the last thing I need.'
I was going to write a joke about paper but it got ripped.
I asked the librarian if they had books on paranoia. She whispered 'They're right behind you.'
I couldn't figure out how to put my seatbelt on. Then it clicked.
I got fired from the keyboard factory because I couldn't find the right keys.
I once got a job in a stamp factory. It was a huge letdown.
I told my wife she should embrace her mistakes. She hugged me.
I got a job at the circus but I was fired for juggling too many tasks.
I started a band called 1023MB. We haven't gotten a gig yet.
I was addicted to drinking brake fluid. But I could stop anytime.
I once had a job at a fire hydrant factory. They said I wasn't very reliable under pressure.
I once worked in a mirror factory. It was something I could really reflect on.
I tried to organize a hide and seek tournament but good players are hard to find.
I named my dog 'Five Miles' so I can tell people I walk Five Miles every day.
I tried to start a hot air balloon business but it never really took off.
I recently got a job at a water park but it turned out to be a splash and dash.
I told a joke about electricity but it was too shocking.
I used to be a carpenter but I just couldn't nail it.
I bought a new pair of shoes and was excited to try them out – they really swept me off my feet.
